            • [ - ] SpiritAnimal - member since 22-Nov-15

              @Calcio_Guy Your wall of text just tells me you don't really know the game. Inter are coming from horrendous seasons, terrible defenses first and consequently bad attacking plays. That's the result of frequently changing coaches. This season, Spalleti began working hard on the physical side and mental side of the players. The players believe in each other and there's a reason they haven't lost a game since June-July. He solidified the defense. That's what builds up confidence and keeps them on every game. Roma, a higher quality team, lost 1-3 at home, and could've been uglier because their players were utterly exhausted after 65 minutes, Inter easily turned the match around after that. Just an example. As for the Juventus-Inter match, Inter had nothing to prove, they know there are at least 3 better teams on paper than them, they don't have to dictate the game in Allianz Stadium. They are building up continuity and team identity, that will be much needed in the coming seasons.
